%N A397163 Decimal expansion of the dihedral angle, in radians, between any two adjacent faces in a canonical (dual-uniform) tetragonal trapezohedron.
%C A397163 The tetragonal trapezohedron is the dual polyhedron of the square antiprism.
%H A397163 Paolo Xausa, <a href="/A397163/b397163.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000</a>
%H A397163 David I. McCooey, <a href="https://dmccooey.com/polyhedra/TetragonalTrapezohedron.html">Tetragonal Trapezohedron</a>.
%H A397163 Polytope Wiki, <a href="https://polytope.miraheze.org/wiki/Square_antitegum">Square antitegum</a>.
%H A397163 Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, <a href="https://mathworld.wolfram.com/Trapezohedron.html">Trapezohedron</a>.
%H A397163 Wikipedia, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tetragonal_trapezohedron">Tetragonal trapezohedron</a>.
%H A397163 <a href="/index/Tra#transcendental">Index entries for transcendental numbers</a>.
%F A397163 Equals arcsec(-1 - sqrt(8)) = arcsec(-1 - A010466).
%F A397163 Equals arccos((1 - sqrt(8))/7) = arccos((1 - A010466)/7).
%F A397163 Equals arccos(c), where c = -0.26120... is the smallest root of 7*x^2 - 2*x - 1.
%e A397163 1.835065491872355962928478692680808140034308009175...
%t A397163 First[RealDigits[ArcSec[-1 - Sqrt[8]], 10, 100]]
%t A397163 (* Alternative: *)
%t A397163 First[RealDigits[First[PolyhedronData[{"Trapezohedron", 4}, "DihedralAngles"]], 10, 100]]
